      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must be under formal configuration management with documented V&V test suite covering hemolysis-relevant flow regimes; all code changes traceable to requirements at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (OpenFOAM 9) operates under version control and has a documented regression test suite. However, hemolysis-specific test cases are not included in the formal SQA suite, and independent code audit has not been performed. Achieved Gradation 3 falls short of the Gradation 4 requirement at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) or equivalent must confirm order-of-accuracy for all governing equations including non-Newtonian constitutive models used in hemolysis prediction.",
      "rationale": "MMS verification was completed for Newtonian Navier-Stokes only. The power-law hemolysis transport equation has not been subjected to formal code verification. Order-of-accuracy confirmation is absent for the primary quantity of interest. Achieved level 2 is substantially below the required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI must be reported for NIH at all five VAD operating points with systematic refinement ratio ≥1.3; extrapolated values must be used in all comparisons to experimental data.",
      "rationale": "GCI study was conducted at design point only (3 meshes, refinement ratio 1.44). Off-design operating points were run on the medium mesh only due to computational cost. Richardson extrapolation was applied at design point (GCI 8.4%) but not at off-design points. Partial compliance yields achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "In-vitro test conditions must replicate all five COU operating points with documented uncertainty on flow rate (±2%), rotational speed (±0.5%), and fluid temperature (±0.5°C); blood analog rheology must be characterized per ASTM F1841.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro experiments were performed at four of five target operating points; the highest-shear condition (6000 rpm, 2 L/min) was not tested due to pump durability concerns. Blood analog rheology was characterized but temperature control uncertainty was ±1.2°C, exceeding the ±0.5°C requirement. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., validation metric M) must be computed with full uncertainty propagation for NIH at all five operating points; comparison must account for both experimental and simulation uncertainty bands.",
      "rationale": "NIH comparisons were performed at four operating points with simulation uncertainty from Monte Carlo UQ. Experimental uncertainty was estimated but not formally propagated into the validation metric. The highest-shear point is absent. Systematic over-prediction by factor 1.4–2.1 indicates model-form inadequacy beyond numerical uncertainty. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validation QoI (NIH) must be directly the COU QoI; no surrogate quantities acceptable at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis is both the validation and COU quantity of interest. No surrogate or intermediate quantities were used. The mapping from computational hemolysis scalar to NIH follows the ASTM F1841 protocol. This factor is satisfied at required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must be conducted on the actual device geometry or a geometrically identical surrogate under COU flow conditions; FDA generic pump geometry may be used only if geometric similarity to the submission device is documented.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic centrifugal pump, which shares topological similarity with the submission device but differs in impeller blade count (5 vs. 6) and volute exit angle. Geometric similarity documentation was provided but does not include quantitative hemolysis sensitivity to these geometric differences. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence, round-off, and time-stepping errors must be quantified and shown to be negligible relative to discretization error for all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence was monitored via residual norms but no formal quantification of solver error contribution to NIH was performed. Round-off error analysis was not conducted. This factor was identified as an epistemic gap at MRL 5 and flagged as not-assessed; achieved level assigned 1 by default."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation protocol with independent review of boundary condition setup, material property assignment, and post-processing scripts for NIH calculation.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of simulation setup was performed. Boundary conditions and material property assignments were set by the same analyst who performed post-processing. Use error is a known gap flagged at MRL 5; not-assessed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The hemolysis constitutive model must be justified against mechanistic red blood cell damage data; alternative model forms must be evaluated; model-form uncertainty must be quantified and shown to be within acceptable bounds for absolute threshold decisions.",
      "rationale": "The power-law Giersiepen-Wurzinger model was used without evaluation of mechanistic alternatives (e.g., strain-based or energy dissipation models). Monte Carlo UQ identified model-form uncertainty as the dominant variance source (Sobol S1=0.61). No model-form uncertainty bounding analysis was performed to justify the power-law choice for absolute predictions. Achieved level 2 against required level 5 represents the largest credibility gap in this assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters (geometry, boundary conditions, material properties, hemolysis model constants) must have documented uncertainty characterization; distributions must be based on measurement data or published literature with traceability.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity and hemolysis power-law constants were assigned distributions based on published literature (Sobol analysis inputs). Pump geometry tolerances were estimated from manufacturing specifications without direct measurement. Inlet flow waveform uncertainty was not characterized. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Physical test samples must be characterized for geometric fidelity to CAD nominal; sample-to-sample variability in hemolysis measurements must be quantified across at least three independent pump units.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro hemolysis experiments were conducted on a single pump unit. Sample-to-sample geometric variability and its effect on NIH were not assessed. This is a critical gap for a Class III device at MRL 5; flagged as not-assessed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Equivalency between validation experiment input parameters and COU input parameters must be formally demonstrated, including fluid rheology, operating pressure, and temperature; any deviations must be shown to have negligible effect on NIH.",
      "rationale": "The validation experiments used a phosphate-buffered saline/glycerol blood analog. Equivalency of this analog to human blood under VAD shear conditions has not been formally demonstrated for the hemolysis QoI. Temperature deviations (±1.2°C vs. ±0.5°C required) were not shown to be negligible. Flagged as not-assessed at MRL 5."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou2-vad-not-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All thirteen credibility factors have been evaluated against MRL 5 requirements. Seven factors were formally assessed; six remain not-assessed, representing epistemic gaps that cannot be closed within the current evidence base. The most critical gap is model form (achieved 2, required 5): the power-law hemolysis constitutive model dominates prediction variance (Sobol S1=0.61 per the Monte Carlo UQ campaign) and has not been justified against mechanistic alternatives. Output comparison shows systematic over-prediction by factor 1.4–2.1, which precludes reliable absolute threshold decisions for a Class III device. The assessment team concludes that the computational model does not meet the credibility requirements for COU2 at MRL 5. Submission is not accepted pending resolution of model-form uncertainty, completion of multi-unit experimental testing, and formal equivalency demonstration for blood analog rheology.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
